a Galactica". Cosmos: A Personal Voyage. Episode 12. 01:24 minutes in. PBS.  101. ^ Rawson, Hugh (2008). "Sagan's Standard". The Unwritten Laws of Life. CSBC Ltd. Archived from the original on January 12, 2012. Retrieved September 1, 2013.  102. ^ Truzzi, Marcello (1978). "On the Extraordinary: An Attempt at Clarification" (PDF). Zetetic Scholar. 1 (1): 11.  103. ^ Truzzi, Marcello (1998). Binkowski, Edward, ed. "On Some Unfair Practices towards Claims of the Paranormal". Oxymoron: Annual Thematic Anthology of the Arts and Sciences. New York: Oxymoron Media, Inc. 2: The Fringe. ISSN 1090-2236. OCLC 35240974. Retrieved September 1, 2013.  104. ^ Flournoy, Théodore (1983) [Originally published 1899; Geneva: Édition Atar]. Des Indes à la Planète Mars: Étude sur un cas de Somnambulisme avec Glossolalie [From India to the Planet Mars: A Study of a Case of Somnambulism with Glossolalia] (in French). Introduction by Hélène Boursinhac; translation by Daniel B. Vermilye (Reprint ed.). Geneva: Éditions Slatkine. pp. 344–345. ISBN 2-05-100499-4. OCLC 11558608.  105. ^ Sagan 1980 (1985 ed.), p. 108  106. ^ Grinspoon, Lester (1994) [2nd ed. published 1977; Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press]. Marihuana Reconsidered. New introduction by author (2nd (reprint) ed.). Oakland, CA: Quick American Archives. ISBN 0-932551-13-0. LCCN 77076767. OCLC 32410025.  107. ^ Sagan, Carl. "Mr. X". Marijuana-Uses.com. Retrieved August 7, 2009.  108. ^ Whitehouse, David (October 15, 1999). "Carl Sagan: A life in the cosmos". BBC News. BBC. Retrieved August 30, 2013.  109. ^ Davidson, Keay (August 22, 1999). "Billions and Billions of '60s Flashbacks". The San Francisco Examiner. Retrieved May 2, 2007.  110. ^ Larsen, Dana (November 1, 1999). "Carl Sagan: toking astronomer". Cannabis Culture. Vancouver, B.C. Retrieved May 2, 2007.  111. ^ "Foundation Board of Directors". NORML.org. Washington, D.C.: NORML and the NORML Foundation. August 13, 2010. Archived from the original on January 4, 2011. Re