 Annie; John T Cullen; the staff of Deep Outside SFFH (November 2002). "About Philip K. Dick: An interview with Tessa, Chris, and Ranea Dick". Deep Outside SFFH. Far Sector SFFH. Retrieved April 14, 2008.  50. ^ "Philip K. Dick Films". Philip K. Dick Trust. August 11, 2009. Archived from the original on August 22, 2010. Retrieved September 3, 2010.  51. ^ Kermode, Mark (July 15, 2000). On the Edge of Bladerunner (TV documentary). UK: Channel 4.  52. ^ Dick, Philip K. "Letter to Jeff Walker regarding "Blade Runner"". Archived from the original on December 13, 2003. Retrieved May 31, 2016.  53. ^ Roberts, Randall. "calendarlive.com". calendarlive.com. Archived from the original on December 11, 2007. Retrieved November 12, 2013.  54. ^ "Ubik (2010) - Preview". Sci-Fi Movie Page. Retrieved November 12, 2013.  55. ^ Philip K. Dick's 'Flow My Tears, the Policeman Said' Being Adapted Alex Billington, FirstShowing.net, May 12, 2009  56. ^ Sweney, Mark (October 7, 2010). "Ridley Scott to return to work of sci-fi icon for BBC mini-series: Blade Runner director to executive produce four-part BBC1 adaptation of Philip K Dick's The Man in the High Castle". The Observer.  57. ^ "Amazon.com: The Man In The High Castle – Season 1: Alexa Davalos, Rupert Evans, Luke Kleintank, DJ Qualls, Joel De La Fuente, Cary Hiroyuki-Tagawa, Rufus Sewell, David Semel, Daniel Percival, Ken Olin, Michael Rymer, Bryan Spicer, Nelson Mccormick, Brad Anderson, Karyn Kusama, Michael Slovis, Frank Spotnitz, Thomas Schnauz, Evan Wright, Jace Richdale, Rob Williams, Emma Frost, Walon Green, Ridley Scott, David W. Zucker, Isa Dick Hackett, Christopher Tricarico, Stewart Mackinnon, Chrtistian Baute, Richard Heus, Dan Percival, Jordan Sheehan, Kalen Egan, Erin Smith, Philip K. Dick".  58. ^ Patten, Dominic (July 21, 2018). "'Man In The High Castle' Renewed For Season 4; Unveils Season 3 Premiere Date & Trailer – Comic-Con". Deadline. Retrieved July 22, 2018.  59. ^ Cynthia Littleton. "Amazon Grabs U.S. Rights to Bryan Cranston's 'Philip K. Dick's Electric Dreams' Anthology Series". Variety.  60. ^ Lodderhose, Diana (May 10, 2016). "Bryan Cranston to Star in Philip K. Dick Series From 'Outlander's' Ron Moore". variety.com. Retrieved May 11, 2016.  61. ^ "evidEnce room – past productions". Archived from the original on February 7, 2012.  62. ^ Foley, Kathleen (April 22, 1999). "'Flow My Tears' Has Hallucinatory Style". Los Angeles Times. Retrieved May 28, 2012.  63. ^ "Archived NTK email newsletter from 11 June 1999". Ntk.net. Retrieved November 12, 2013.  64. ^ Zinoman, Jason (December 3, 2010). "A Test for Humanity in a Post-Apocalyptic World". The New York Times.  65. ^ "The Defenders". Project Gutenberg.  66. ^ "Przedstawienie Trzy stygmaty Palmera Eldritcha". encyklopediateatru.pl. Retrieved October 10, 2016.  67. ^ "Trzy stygmaty Palmera Eldritcha – Stary Teatr". krakow.wyborcza.pl. Retrieved October 10, 2016.  68. ^ "Episode 1, Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?, Dangerous Visions - BBC Radio 4". BBC.  69. ^ "MARVEL BRINGS PHILIP K DICK'S ELECTRIC ANT TO LIFE IN NEW SERIES". philipkdick.com. July 24, 2008. Archived from the original on August 12, 2012.  70. ^ SDCC 08: PHILIP K. DICK COMES TO MARVEL www.ign.com  71. ^ Philip K. Dick Press Release – BOOM! ANNOUNCES DO ANDROIDS DREAM OF ELECTRIC SHEEP? Archived September 20, 2012, at the Wayback Machine.  72. ^ TOTAL RECALL #1 (OF 4) www.dynamite.com  73. ^ Total Recall #1 www.comicvine.com  74. ^ The Selected Letters of Philip K. Dick, 1975–1976. Novato, California : Underwood-Miller, 1993 (Trade edition) ISBN 0-88733-111-4 p. 240  75. ^ "Home Page of the National Library Service for the Blind and Physically Handicapped (NLS)". Loc.gov. October 28, 2013. Retrieved November 12, 2013.  76. ^ O'Hagen, Sean (June 12, 2005). "What a clever Dick". The Observer. UK. Retrieved April 15, 2008.  77. ^ Taylor, Charles (June 20, 2004). "Just Imagine Philip K. Dick". The New York Times. Retrieved April 15, 2008.  78. ^ Berry, M