ne Found". Toronto: The Globe and Mail, 8 April 2004, p. R6. via ProQuest, 20 September 2011 (subscription); ProQuest Document ID: 1055123471.  62. ^ a b "Antoine de Saint-Exupéry aurait été abattu par un pilote allemand" (in French). Le Monde, 15 March 2008.  63. ^ "Current Exhibitions: IWC-Saint Exupery Space." Archived 2 April 2012 at the Wayback Machine. Association des Amis du Musée de l'Air website, 21 September 2011.  64. ^ a b Rumbold, Richard & Stewart, Lady Margaret. The Winged Life, N.Y.: David McKay Company, 1953. P.214  65. ^ a b Triebel, Claas.The Last Hours of Commander Saint-Exupery, Cicero magazine, 12 April 2008. Retrieved 25 March 2014.  66. ^ a b c d Beale, Nick. "Saint-Exupéry Entre mythe et réalité." Aero Journal, No. 4, 2008, pp. 78–81. More details on the web-site "Ghost Bombers" (see External links)  67. ^ "Saint-Exupéry episode." Ghostbombers.com. Retrieved: 30 September 2012.  68. ^ "Detailansicht".  69. ^ Axel Urbanke: "Green Hearts: First in Combat with the Dora 9", Eagle Editions, 1997, ISBN 978-0966070606.  70. ^ UK National Archives file HW5/548, item CX/MSS/T263/29  71. ^ Tagliabue (2006).  72. ^ "Wartime Author Mystery 'Solved'." BBC News, 17 March 2008.  73. ^ Tagliabue, John. On the Trail of a Missing Aviator, Saint-Exupery The New York Times New York edition, 10 April 2008. Retrieved 25 March 2014.  74. ^ Altweg (2008).  75. ^ Boenisch, Georg & Leick, Romain. Legenden | Gelassen in den Tod, Der Spiegel, 22 March 2008. Retrieved 25 March 2014.  76. ^ "Ivan Rebroffs Bruder schoss Saint-Exupéry ab" (in German). Agence France-Presse, 15 March 2008. Archived 20 March 2008 at the Wayback Machine.  77. ^ German "Pilot fears he killed writer St. Exupéry." Reuters news story quoting Rippert in Le Figaro, 16 March 2008. Retrieved: 16 March 2008. Archived 19 March 2008 at the Wayback Machine.  78. ^ a b Bönisch & Leick (2008).  79. ^ Bobek, Jan.Saint-Exupéry, lack of archival documents, HNED.cz, 29 March 2008. Retrieved 25 March 2014.  80. 